  "text": "To further examine if DNA damage during S-phase can induce p21 accumulation in G2, we treated cells with an ATR kinase inhibitor (ATRi; AZD6738) to induce destablization of stalled DNA replication forks [CITATION_1] . Treatment with ATRi leads to an increase in the proportion of cells with a single gH2AX focus, in the number of gH2AX foci per nucleus, and in p53 expression NATURE COMMUNICATIONS | DOI: 10.1038/ncomms14728 ARTICLE ( Fig. 4c; Supplementary Fig. 5b ). Similar to aphidicolin treatment, cells treated with ATRi display a marked increase in p21-GFP levels in cells in G1, compared to DMSO-treated cells (Fig. 4b) .",
